  "mythology_stories": {
    "intro": "Hod was blind from birth and stood apart from the games when the gods threw weapons at the invulnerable <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Baldr\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=baldur\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Baldr'\">Baldr</a>. <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Loki\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=loki\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Loki'\">Loki</a> approached him and offered to guide his hand, giving him a dart made of mistletoe. When Hod threw it, <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Baldr\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=baldur\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Baldr'\">Baldr</a> fell dead. In revenge, Vali, another <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Son of Odin\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=baldur\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Son of Odin'\">son of Odin</a>, killed Hod while he was only one day old. After <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Ragnarok\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=ragnarok\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Ragnarok'\">Ragnarok</a>, both Hod and <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Baldr\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=baldur\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Baldr'\">Baldr</a> will return from <a class=\"corpus-link\" data-term=\"Hel\" data-tradition=\"norse\" href=\"../corpus-search.html?tradition=norse&amp;term=hel\" title=\"Search corpus for 'Hel'\">Hel</a> to inhabit the renewed world."
